<ul>
    <li>
        The First building Built should be the silo, it costs 100 Stones, 10
        Clay, and 5 copperbars. The silo is able to stock Hay to feed your
        animals so you dont have to buy it at Marnie's for 50g a piece. (it also
        feel s like she is never in her store...)
    </li>
    <li>
        using your scythe you can cut the grs on the farm and if you have a silo
        hay will be stocked automatically.
    </li>
    <li>
        when going fishing or mining you can bring a chest so that your are not
        limited by your inventory slots. however be carefull not to place them
        in spaces where villagers walk as they will destroy the chests.
    </li>
    <li>
        In the mines combat does not take up energy so if you are low, focus on
        the monsters as they can spawn stars aswell.
    </li>
    <li>
        You should alwaysbring artifacts to Gunther at the museum as he gives
        rewards such as seeds, furniture, and farm equipment etc.
    </li>
</ul>
